Colombian Stocks: Avianca Taca, Colinversiones, Fabricato

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-05-16T16:14:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/colombian-stocks-avianca-taca-colinversiones-fabricato.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:45 a.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 0.1 percent to 14,245.60, while the
Colcap Index was little changed at 1,708.  Avianca Taca Holding SA (PFAVTA CB), owner of  Colombia ’s
biggest airline, gained 0.6 percent to 5,340 pesos. The
company’s expansion plan is on schedule “which means better
results and synergies will come in the next quarters,”
brokerage Interbolsa SA said in an e-mailed report today.  Cia. Colombiana de Inversiones SA (COLINV CB) rose 0.2
percent to 4,995 pesos after the company agreed May 13 to sell
its shares in Articulos de Seguridad SA, Prevencionistas en
Ambiente, Salud y Seguridad SA, and Compania Latinoamericano de
Seguridad Industrial SA to Northbay Invest Colombia SA, an
affiliate of Capital Safety Group. The operations had a value of
about 101 billion pesos ($56 million), according to a regulatory
filing.  Textiles Fabricato SA (FABRI CB), Colombia’s biggest
textile maker, fell 2.9 percent to 51 pesos, the most since
March 30 on an intraday basis. The White House threatened to
hold up final passage of a trade agreement with Colombia unless
lawmakers expand retraining assistance for American workers who
lose jobs to foreign competitors, the AP reported today.  Banco Popular SA (POPULA)   fell 7.7 percent to 600 pesos,
its lowest since Jan. 13 on an intraday basis. Luis Carlos
Sarmiento, chairman of Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores SA (AVAL
CB), said Colombia’s biggest financial holding company will have
“absolute control” of Popular once it buys a majority stake in
the bank.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
